@{ 
    ViewData["Title"] = "Cookies";
    Layout = "_Layout";
}

<div class="grid-row">
    <div class="column-two-thirds">
        <a class="link-back" asp-controller="Dashboard" asp-action="Index">Home</a>
        <h1 class="heading-xlarge">Cookies</h1>
        <p>This service website puts small files (known as 'cookies') onto your computer.</p>
        <p>These cookies are used to:</p>
        <ul class="list list-bullet">
            <li>help us understand how you use the website, so we can make improvements </li>
            <li>remember what notifications you've seen so you're not shown them more than once</li>
            <li>temporarily store the selections you make</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Find out more about
            <a rel="external" href="https://ico.org.uk/for-the-public/online/cookies/">how to manage cookies</a>.</p>

        <h2 class="heading-medium" id="end-point-assessor-cookies">Session cookies</h2>

        <p>We store session cookies on your computer to help keep your information secure while you use the service website. A session is the time you spend using the service website.</p>

        <table class="table-font-xsmall table-spaced">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                  <th>Name</th>
                  <th>Purpose</th>
                  <th>Expires</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                  <td>.Assessors.Cookies, .Apply.Cookies</td>
                  <td>These are the authentication cookies</td>
                  <td>When you sign out or the session expires</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                  <td>.Assessors.Session, .Apply.Session</td>
                  <td>These cookies hold the session data</td>
                  <td>When you sign out or the session expires</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                  <td>.Assessors.AntiForgery, .Apply.AntiForgery</td>
                  <td>Ensure that only our website can send information to our servers</td>
                  <td>When you sign out or the session expires</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <h2 class="heading-medium" id="measuring-website-usage-google-analytics">Measuring website usage</h2>

        <p>We use Google Analytics software to collect information about how you use the service website. This information helps us to improve the service.</p>

        <p>We don't collect or store your personal information (for example, your name or address) so this information can't be used to identify who you are.</p>

        <h3 class="heading-small" id="google-analytics-cookies">Google Analytics cookies</h3>

        <p>Google Analytics cookies collect and store information about:</p>

        <ul class="list list-bullet">
            <li>the pages you visit</li>
            <li>how you got to the service</li>
            <li>what you click on while you're visiting the website</li>
        </ul>

        <div role="note" aria-label="Information" class="application-notice info-notice">
            <p>We don't allow Google to use or share our analytics data, but you can
                <a rel="external" href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout">opt out of analytics cookies</a>.</p>
        </div>

        <p>Google Analytics sets the following cookies:</p>

        <table class="table-font-xsmall">
            <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Name</th>
                <th>Purpose</th>
                <th>Expires</th>
            </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>_ga</td>
                <td>This cookie helps us understand how you have used the service</td>
                <td>2 years</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>_gat</td>
                <td>Used to manage the rate at which page view requests are made</td>
                <td>10 minutes</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>_gid</td>
                <td>This helps us track how many people visit the service website</td>
                <td>24 hours</td>
            </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <h2 class="heading-medium" id="introductory-message">Introductory message cookie</h2>

        <p>You may see a pop-up welcome message when you first visit the service website. We'll store a cookie so that your computer knows you've seen it and knows not to show it again.</p>
        <table class="table-font-xsmall">
            <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Name</th>
                <th>Purpose</th>
                <th>Expires</th>
            </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>seen_cookie_message</td>
                <td>Saves a message to let us know that you've seen our cookie message</td>
                <td>1 month</td>
            </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <h2 class="heading-medium" id="govuk-messages">Messages across GOV.UK</h2>

        <p>We might display a message on all GOV.UK pages to tell you about an important event or situation. We'll save a cookie that will let us know how many times you've seen it, or if you've dismissed it.</p>

        <table class="table-font-xsmall">
            <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Name</th>
                <th>Purpose</th>
                <th>Expires</th>
            </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>global_bar_seen</td>
                <td>Remembers the number of times you've seen the message, or if you've dismissed it</td>
                <td>12 weeks</td>
            </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <h2 class="heading-medium" id="our-performance-survey">Our performance survey</h2>

        <p>We select some users to take part in a performance survey. If you take part, or dismiss the survey, we'll save a cookie that lets us know you've seen the message so that we don't show it to you again.</p>

        <table class="table-spaced table-font-xsmall">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Name</th>
                    <th>Purpose</th>
                    <th>Expires</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>govuk_takenUserSatisfactionSurvey</td>
                    <td>Saves a message to remember if you've taken the survey or dismissed it</td>
                    <td>4 months</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <p>We use <a href="https://www.smartsurvey.co.uk">SmartSurvey</a> to collect responses to the survey. If you take part, SmartSurvey will save extra cookies to your computer to track your progress through it.</p>

        <table class="table-font-xsmall">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Name</th>
                    <th>Purpose</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>ASP.NET_SessionId, SX_X, _ga, _gat_X, _gid</td>
                    <td>We use SmartSurvey for the performance survey on this service website. For more information, please <a href="https://www.smartsurvey.co.uk/privacy-policy">see SmartSurvey privacy information</a>.</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </div>
</div>